      "@type": "Dataset",
      "identifier": "ssbd-repos-000453",
      "name": "microtubule-dependent nuclear transport in neurons driven by Nesprin-2 and microtubule motors",
      "description": "This study identifies Nesprin-2 as a bidirectional motor adaptor during nuclear migration in developing neurons. Nesprin-2 coordinates dynein complex and kinesin-1 and activates prolonged bidirectional movements of the nucleus along forward moving microtubules in migrating neurons.",
